\par           - what this gives you is a single-click winamp server.
\par           The server can be monitored by going to Plugins > General > Configure and selecting the pmmsoft RPC
\par           interface entry.
\par           The server can be configured to use different ports on the fly, and the settings are persistent.
\par           Warnings are issued for all RFC1060 ports (which didn't include http ?!) -and http.
\par           You should only use such ports if you really have to, and you know what you are doing. 
\par           new features to the interface
\par                The client remembers the endpoint settings at the last shutdown, and also hides itself to the taskbar if
\par                it was shut down from the taskbar, but only if the initial connect to the server was successful. 
\par                The client can now show the current song title, and the winamp version. 
\par                The full playlist is available, and can be deleted/added to using add files with a right-click menu. 
\par }\pard\plain \s3\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \f1\lang2057\cgrid {     05/03/00 third release - major upgrade of the interface
