\par           The server interface is independent of the previous version, and they can run side by side. 
\par           Winamp status is now returned!
\par           Winamp's playing status is polled every second, where the RPC call succeeds, and every 5s after a failure.
\par           The status is displayed on the new-look form and the taskbar. 
\par           Client is now registry aware - settings are per user, and loaded/saved on startup/shutdown.
\par           Some more options, and a few cosmetic alterations. 
\par           Pause now checks for the status, and displays the appropriate action.
\par           More crucially, pause checks winamp's state and only pauses where appropriate (this can catch people
\par           out otherwise in an office). 
\par           The old style interface for sending strings appears to be broken in winamp V2.6 (access violation and
